# Ontology Feature Requests

When the user says "add feature" without another explicit target, interpret it
as a request to add an ontology feature entry to:

`docs/specs/ontology-features.md`

Use the existing feature template in that document. Include:

- intent;
- ontology scope;
- upper-ontology or external-vocabulary alignment;
- candidate classes/properties/concepts;
- integration points;
- privacy/access notes;
- open questions.

Do not implement contracts, ontology TTL files, database schema, or UI unless
the user explicitly asks for implementation.
